It is the expectation within Respite Care of San Antonio (RCSA) that all medication be appropriately stored within a locked container only accessible to staff given permission to administer medication. No child is permitted to possess any medication within their own room, on their person, or in any capacity unless otherwise instructed by the Treatment Director, LCCA, Or Designee. All medications, including OTC medication, must be stored within the Davidson Respite House (DRH), double locked behind the Medication Closet and the Medication Cart. There is no exception to this rule. Should a staff member become aware of any violations to this procedure, they are to immediately report the violation to the Quality Improvement Specialist, Treatment Director, LCCA, or Designee. Failure to do so, or failure to immediately remedy the violation will result in disciplinary action. 

